def: The bell of a sessile gonozooid.

Causing weariness; tiresome; tedious; weariful; as, a wearisomemarch; a wearisome day's work; a wearisome book.These high wild hills and rough uneven ways Draws out our miles, andmakes them wearisome. Shak.
Relating to, or having the nature of, a demon. "Demonianspirits." Milton.
They say, or it is said.-- n.
Foil or wire made of gold, silver, or brass. De Colange.
Proceeding by the smaller intervals (half steps or semitones)of the scale, instead of the regular intervals of the diatonic scale.
